=head1 NAME

<Entity::Component::[% component_name %]> <[% component_name %] component concret class>

=head1 VERSION

This documentation refers to <Entity::Component::[% component_name %]> version 1.0.0.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

use <Entity::Component::[% component_name %]>;

my $component_instance_id = 2; # component instance id

Entity::Component::[% component_name %]->get(id=>$component_instance_id);

# Cluster id

my $cluster_id = 3;

# Component id are fixed, please refer to component id table

my $component_id =2 

Entity::Component::[% component_name %]->new(component_id=>$component_id, cluster_id=>$cluster_id);

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Entity::Component::[% component_name %] is class allowing to instantiate a [% component_name %] component
This Entity is empty but present methods to set configuration.

=head1 METHODS

=cut

package Entity::Component::[% component_name %];
